column5: Just curious to see who is from Sturgeon ....or close to Sturgeon....  :Gonefishing:   Randy From Sturgeon
3 hours west in Elliot Lake
Hey Randy, how about organizing a swill. We can all bunk at TJ's for the weekend.
Sounds Good to me!!!!         T.J   ??????  T.J??????
Mom's from Sturgeon!  Aubin is the family name..  How's it hanging up there in Sturg town bud?!  HD
Crash, err, Cache Bay.
I know a few Aubin from up here..I fish with one....went to school with some...bought wood from another..  Everything is good in Sturgeon !~!
I'm here Huckelberry!!
The Shanks say hello!  Mario can't put a finger on you cause I don't know yer real name...  but he says"  Ahh Oui! Je pense que je sais qui tu veut dire"  "Dit s'y allo pour moi"
Grand-parents used to own Camp la Plage..   You may have fished with some of my folk..  That's pretty rad!!
A Sturgeon Falls swill? At Tj's ? Hmmmmm OK!!!!! When?
......Eh!     T.J.    ????  I think he's ignoring this post !!
Hey TJ! For a two-four I can misplace this thread.
Hey Randy, I almost feel like a homeboy in Sturgeon Falls, cause everytime I come thru town I run into you at Timmies  See you next June, August & September
I am not from there, but I have a bunch of friends in Field/River Valley.  I love heading up there, the fishing is awesome.  Thinking of moving up there eventually!
Twice a year I call it home, at least the truck, which stays there while I fish the French.  I have a couple swills each year at TJ's too.    God, life is good up there.
Umm... were going to be away that weekend... lol...  Sturgmans from sturgeon......
No, not that weekend TJ, the weekend following. The lovely Monique already OK'd it.
Umm no...  were busy then too.
My family is from Cache Bay! Larocque's
